  "description": [
    "I EDUCATION IN THE SOVIET UNION ILS ExtraCurricular Programs Rated Superior to Soviet Schools By DR GEORGE V KIRK I I EDITORS NOTE This is the seventh in a series of ar tides written especially for this paper by Dr Kirk su perintendent of Smyrna Special Schools on his re cent trip to the Soviet Un ion Questions addressed to the author concerning the trip people living condi tions etc behind the Iron Curtain may be sent to The Smyrna Times Kirk Pro ject 2527 Commerce St Smyrna Delaware Many people on hearing the heavy academic program of the Soviet Union tend to assume that the educational program of the Soviet schools stops there This is not true In the first place as has already been men tioned the Soviet schools offer art and singing in grades 1 thru 6 for one hour per week handi crafts in grades 1 thru 7 for 1 or 2 hours per week and physi cal education throughout the en tire tenyear school for 2 hours per week We saw students par ticipating in these programs within the schools While the art followed the usual Soviet pat tern everyone in the class was drawing"
  ],
